# LAGUNA BEACH TENNIS ACADEMY — CURSOR RULES
# "Tennis, as it should be taught. Movement. Discipline. Belonging."
# Last Updated: December 24, 2025

## Project Identity

You are building the Laguna Beach Tennis Academy (LBTA) website — a premium, founder-led tennis academy in Laguna Beach, California. This is NOT a generic sports website. It's a cinematic, luxury digital experience that embodies the philosophy: "Movement. Discipline. Belonging."

**Brand DNA:**
- Founder: Andrew Mateljan (25+ years tennis experience, ATP/WTA coaching)
- Mission: Excellence built through movement-first coaching and community
- Tone: Calm, authentic, confident — never salesy or hyperbolic
- Aesthetic: Luxury restraint meets California warmth (Aman/Four Seasons digital presence)

---

## Tech Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 14.2+ (App Router)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS 3.4+
- **Animation:** Framer Motion 11+
- **Language:** TypeScript 5.3+
- **Fonts:** Playfair Display (serif headlines) + Work Sans (body)
- **Deployment:** Vercel
- **CRM Integration:** ActiveCampaign

---

## Core Design Principles

### 1. Mobile-First Responsive Design
```
Breakpoints (test every change at ALL sizes):
- 320px  → Mobile small (iPhone SE)
- 375px  → Mobile standard (iPhone 14)
- 768px  → Tablet
- 1024px → Desktop small
- 1440px → Desktop large
```

### 2. Performance Standards (Non-Negotiable)
```
- LCP (Largest Contentful Paint): < 2.5s
- CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift): < 0.1
- INP (Interaction to Next Paint): < 100ms
- Lighthouse Score: ≥ 90 in all categories
```

### 3. Accessibility Standards (WCAG 2.1 AAA)
```
- Color Contrast: 7:1 ratio minimum for text
- Touch Targets: 48×48px minimum on mobile
- Keyboard Navigation: All interactive elements accessible
- Screen Readers: Semantic HTML + ARIA labels on all media
- Focus States: Visible 2px orange (#F8A121) outline
- Reduced Motion: Respect prefers-reduced-motion
```

### 4. Luxury Perception Architecture
```
- White Space: 40%+ negative space required
- Color Palette: 11 colors maximum (see tokens below)
- Typography: Serif headlines + sans-serif body
- Animation: Slow, intentional (200-300ms), spring-based
- CTAs: Refined, confident — avoid garish buttons
- Imagery: High-quality WebP, editorial feel, no stock photos
- Copy: Concise, confident, no hyperbole or marketing speak
```

